The paper introduces a new neural network architecture called Grid Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) that can be applied to vectors, sequences, and higher dimensional data such as images. The network is designed to provide a unified way of using LSTM for both deep and sequential computation. The paper presents results for algorithmic tasks such as 15-digit integer addition and sequence memorization, as well as empirical tasks such as character prediction and Chinese-to-English translation. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper deals with neural network architectures and natural language processing tasks. Other possible sub-categories include cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper also deals with image data and general machine learning tasks.
